# GreenEyes NYC — Reduction Monitor

> Intelligent energy reduction monitoring for NYC buildings. Real-time LL97 compliance, carbon tracking, and automated alerts.

---

## Project Overview

GreenEyes NYC is a 6-page marketing + product website showcasing a smart energy monitoring platform built for NYC buildings subject to Local Law 97 (LL97).

### 6-Page Structure

| Page | Section | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| 1 | Intro | Grass green background, animated wires, left-aligned tagline |
| 2 | NYC Landscape | City skyline + feature circles (Saving, Reliable, Fast, Free) |
| 3 | Dashboard | Full live reduction monitor — gigantic product view |
| 4 | Devices | iPad + 4 iPhone 17 mockups showing live features |
| 5 | Features | Blueprint building illustration + 5 feature buttons + half-iPad |
| 6 | Outro | Grass green, wires, right-aligned closing tagline |

---

## Tech Stack

### Frontend
- **React 18** + **Vite** — fast dev server with HMR
- **Tailwind CSS v3** — utility-first styling
- **Recharts** — energy bar chart, compliance graphs
- **Axios** — HTTP client with mock data fallbacks

### Backend
- **Node.js** + **Express** — REST API server
- **better-sqlite3** — embedded SQLite, zero config
- **CORS** — configured for localhost:3000

---

## Data Sources → UI Components

| Source | Powers |
|--------|--------|
| `buildings` + `ll97_limits` + `compliance_snapshots` | Fine Risk Meter, Compliance bars, Countdown, Building Selector |
| `energy_readings` | 7-day Energy Chart, Current Usage KPI, Floor Heatmap |
| `solar_readings` | Solar Output KPI, Solar Performance card, AC/E/H scores |
| `alerts` | Alert count KPI, Bell badge, Alert list panel |
| `sensors` | Systems Status card, Live status dot in header |
| `floors` + `energy_readings` | 30-cell floor energy grid |
| `users` + `user_buildings` | User avatar, Building dropdown, Notification routing |

---

## API Endpoints That Use React

All endpoints under `/api/` are called with `useEffect` + `useState` on **Page 3 (Dashboard)**.

| Endpoint | Hook | Component |
|----------|------|-----------|
| `GET /api/buildings` | `useEffect` | `BuildingSelector` |
| `GET /api/buildings/:id/compliance` | `useEffect` | `FineRiskMeter`, `ComplianceProgress`, `CountdownTimer` |
| `GET /api/energy/:id?days=7` | `useEffect` | `EnergyChart` |
| `GET /api/energy/:id/current` | `useEffect` | `KPICard` (Current Usage) |
| `GET /api/energy/:id/floors` | `useEffect` | `FloorHeatmap` |
| `GET /api/solar/:id` | `useEffect` | `KPICard` (Solar Output), `SolarWidget` |
| `GET /api/alerts/:id` | `useEffect` | `AlertsPanel`, bell badge count |
| `GET /api/sensors/:id` | `useEffect` | `SystemsStatus` |

Pages 4 & 5 use **embedded mock data** (no API calls needed) for device mockup display.

